OL,3,CFirms 'may need to be forced to accept
OL,4,Ccash to prevent two-tier society'
OL,6,FNot doing so could risk creating a two-
OL,7,Ftier society, where vulnerable groups
OL,8,Fbecome excluded from community spaces
OL,9,Fsuch as leisure centres, theatres and
OL,10,Fpublic transport, it added.
OL,12,FThe committee said it has heard from
OL,13,Fthose representing vulnerable sectors
OL,14,Fof society, including people with
OL,15,Flearning disabilities, domestic abuse
OL,16,Fvictims and the elderly, that buying
OL,17,Fessential goods and services can cost
OL,18,Fmore, as the number of places where
OL,19,Fthey can spend coins and banknotes
OL,20,Fshrinks.
