OL,6,FIt added: "For people who do not have
OL,7,Fbank accounts, who are sometimes
OL,8,Freferred to as the 'unbanked', being
OL,9,Fable to spend physical cash is vital."
OL,11,FThe committee also heard that people
OL,12,Fwith learning disabilities were more
OL,13,Flikely to need to rely on cash and
OL,14,Fcould be severely impacted by cash
OL,15,Fbeing refused as a form of payment.
OL,17,FSurvivors of economic abuse meanwhile
OL,18,Fmay rely on cash to get by and to
OL,19,Fescape their abusers.
